section:
PEAR_Error [deprecated]PEAR Error object





   PEAR_Error is an object created by
   every function in PEAR in case of a failure. It provides information
   on why a function fails.



   How you get the object depends on

    PEAR::SetErrorHandling


  &core.pear.pear-error.adduserinfo;
  &core.pear.pear-error.getcallback;  
  &core.pear.pear-error.getcode;  
  &core.pear.pear-error.getmessage;  
  &core.pear.pear-error.getmode;
  &core.pear.pear-error.getdebuginfo;
  &core.pear.pear-error.gettype;  
  &core.pear.pear-error.getuserinfo;  
  &core.pear.pear-error.pear-error;
  &core.pear.pear-error.tostring;
